      </svg>
      <p>
        <strong>Anthropic (2024),</strong>
        <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Model Context Protocol Specification.</em></a>
        Open standard for connecting AI models to external tools and
        data sources. The specification defines how tools advertise their
        capabilities, how models request tool calls, and how results are
        returned.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>The Full Arc: Five Days, One Toolkit</h3>
    <p>
      The progression across the course has been deliberate. Day 1 built
      the foundations: how models represent meaning and generate text.
      Days 2 and 3 taught you to control models: prompting, validation,
      fine-tuning, APIs at scale. Day 4 applied these skills to research
      tasks: extraction, RAG, working with large corpora. Day 5 showed
      how to orchestrate all of these into autonomous workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each day's tools became the next day's building blocks. Day 1's
      embeddings powered Day 4's retrieval. Day 2's prompting skills
      shaped Day 4's extraction prompts and Day 5's system prompt.
      Day 3's validation framework carried through as the faithfulness
      checks in Days 4 and 5. And Day 4's functions became Day 5's
      agent tools.
    </p>

